                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1219.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-27T14:00:00-04:49">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1915—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>French Legation threatened and a forcible entry attempted for the purpose of
                    taking out the President. French Minister and British Chargé d’Affaires have
                    telegraphed for ships. Situation very grave and the presence of war vessels as
                    soon as possible necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
